        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: This figure shows that neurofilament light chain (NF-L) can be detected by immunofluorescence in presynaptic terminals of the neuromuscular junction in mice.. Experimental description: figure legend \"Representative confocal micrographs of NMJs showing higher levels of NF-L than NF-M in motor nerve terminals and axon terminal protrusions (arrows) in the LAL of a C57BL/6 mouse at P10\"" ;
